The paper proposes a new approach to speech enhancement using generative adversarial networks. This work involves deep learning and signal processing, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper also involves natural language processing, which is relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of deep networks and large example sets suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the evaluation of the proposed model involves both objective and subjective evaluations, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the waveform-level processing and end-to-end training suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision), although this is less likely than the other categories.
